<recipe>
<title>
Buttered Parsley Potato Recipe
</title>
<details>
AUTHOR: I Heart Eating
PREP TIME: 15 minutes
COOK TIME: 25 minutes
TOTAL TIME: 40 minutes
COURSE: Side Dish
CUISINE: American
KEYWORD: potatoes
SERVINGS: 6 servings
</details>
<ingredients>
1 1/2 lbs . gold creamer potatoes*
1/4 c . butter
1/4-1/2 tsp . kosher salt depending on taste preference
1/4 c . parsley
</ingredients>
<instructions>
Rinse potatoes.
Bring a large pot of water to boil.
Add potatoes, and boil for 15 minutes.
Drain potatoes and return to pot.
Add butter and salt to pot, and toss to coat potatoes in butter.
Chop parsley, and sprinkle over potatoes. Toss to combine, if desired.
</instructions>
</recipe>
